Description.LocalizedString: A young woman scorned by humanity, harboring hatred for all but her brother.
A moth-eaten rag that smells of sweat and smoke.
Tales warned of a demon who skulked the gutters of Marseille with shimmering blade in hand. In reality, it was a battered sickle Charlotte stole from a farmer’s home and modified to her liking.
She wanted only to inflict humanity with the cruelty they had inflicted upon her family.
A moth-eaten rag that smells of the viscera upon it.
The sickle once seen in the streets of Marseille has been busy.
A woman who witnessed her parents’ disappearance and found clues to their fate in occult artifacts.
A loose-fitting, long-sleeved crop top. The pendant was a gift from Élodie’s mother, received days before their final trip together.
Pants that weren’t specifically made for Élodie, but they fit like they were.
A comfortable crop top that’s shared many adventures with Élodie.
A woman who witnessed her parents’ disappearance and found herself on a similar, bloody path.
A loose-fitting, long-sleeved crop top that’s stained in the blood of many.
Pants that weren’t specifically made for Élodie, though they carry some of her blood.
